Package com.fortify.pub.issueparsing

Contains classes and interfaces for parsing scans and creating issues

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AnalysisFileParser
    Interface for zip file-based parsers (for instance, FPRs)
    AnalysisSingleFileParser
    Interface that can be used by single file-based parsers (for instance, FVDLs)
    BaseAnalysisFileParser
    The base interface for both zip file-based parsers (for example, FPRs) and single file-based parsers (for example, FVDLs)
    IssueHandler
    A generic interface that should be implemented to store issue attributes.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Category
    Created by IntelliJ IDEA.
    NameValuePair
    A simple object for storing a name (or key) along with its value.
    ParsedVulnerability
    Class keeps type and subtype of the vulnerability parsed from input analysis result file.
    PenTestRequest
    Augments Request with information that is specific to pentest issues
    PenTestRequest.Response
    This response represents what the pentesting tool receives in return when it issues a request
    PriorityUtil  
    ReproStep  
    Request
    An abstract class for pentest and runtime issue requests.
    RuntimeRequest
    Augments Request with information that is specific to runtime issues
    Scan
    The scan object contains the general information for the scan, as well as the instance ids of the issues that were included
    Trigger
    A class for representing a single trigger within a pentest request
    UpdateStatus
    An UpdateStatus is used to track the lifecycle of the issue
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    AttackType
    Represents a specific type of attack from a pentesting tool
    PriorityValues
    The possible values for the Fortify Priority Order attribute, which is how issues are divided into folders in the default project template
    ScanCertification
    Represents whether a specific scan is valid or not.
